Here's a practical approach using merged `ResourceDictionary` swapping:

## 1. Define each theme as a separate ResourceDictionary

```xml
<!-- Resources/Styles/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
                    x:Class="MyApp.Resources.Styles.LightTheme">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

```xml
<!-- Resources/Styles/DarkTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary ...
                    x:Class="MyApp.Resources.Styles.DarkTheme">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#1E1E1E</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#E0E0E0</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#4FC3F7</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

```xml
<!-- Resources/Styles/HighContrastTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary ...
                    x:Class="MyApp.Resources.Styles.HighContrastTheme">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#000000</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#FFFF00</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Use the **same keys** in every dictionary — that's what makes the swap seamless.

## 2. Create a theme service

```csharp
public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }

public static class ThemeService
{
    private const string ThemePrefKey = "app_theme";

    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;

        // Remove the current theme dictionary (always the last one added)
        var existing = mergedDicts.FirstOrDefault(d =>
            d is LightTheme or DarkTheme or HighContrastTheme);
        if (existing is not null)
            mergedDicts.Remove(existing);

        // Add the new one
        ResourceDictionary newTheme = theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark         => new DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _                     => new LightTheme()
        };
        mergedDicts.Add(newTheme);

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set(ThemePrefKey, theme.ToString());
    }

    public static AppTheme GetSavedTheme()
    {
        var saved = Preferences.Get(ThemePrefKey, nameof(AppTheme.Light));
        return Enum.TryParse<AppTheme>(saved, out var t) ? t : AppTheme.Light;
    }
}
```

## 3. Apply the saved theme at startup

In `App.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(ThemeService.GetSavedTheme());
}
```

## 4. Build a settings page picker

```xml
<!-- SettingsPage.xaml -->
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker"
        Title="Theme"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged">
    <Picker.ItemsSource>
        <x:Array Type="{x:Type x:String}">
            <x:String>Light</x:String>
            <x:String>Dark</x:String>
            <x:String>HighContrast</x:String>
        </x:Array>
    </Picker.ItemsSource>
</Picker>
```

```csharp
// SettingsPage.xaml.cs
protected override void OnAppearing()
{
    base.OnAppearing();
    ThemePicker.SelectedIndex = (int)ThemeService.GetSavedTheme();
}

void OnThemeChanged(object? sender, EventArgs e)
{
    if (ThemePicker.SelectedIndex < 0) return;
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme((AppTheme)ThemePicker.SelectedIndex);
}
```

## 5. Reference theme colours with `DynamicResource`

This is the critical part — use **`DynamicResource`**, not `StaticResource`, so values update at runtime when the dictionary is swapped:

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" Text="Hello!" />
    <Button BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource Accent}" Text="Go" />
</ContentPage>
```

### Key takeaways

| Concept | Why it matters |
|---|---|
| **Same keys in every dictionary** | Lets you swap dictionaries without touching views |
| **`DynamicResource`** | Re-evaluates when the dictionary changes at runtime |
| **`Preferences`** | Persists the user's choice across app restarts |
| **Swap in `MergedDictionaries`** | Instant app-wide update, no page reload needed |
